---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import BreadcrumbSchema from '../components/schema/BreadcrumbSchema.astro';
import { SITE } from '../consts';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="Percolate terms of service — account, user-generated content, affiliate disclosure, and limitation of liability."
  path="/terms"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <BreadcrumbSchema crumbs={[{ name: 'Terms of Service', url: `${SITE.url}/terms` }]} />
  </Fragment>

  <p class="brand">{SITE.name}</p>
  <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
  <p class="effective">Effective Date: May 13, 2026</p>

  <p>
    These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your use of Percolate ("the
    app") and the website at <a href={SITE.url}>{SITE.url}</a>. By using the
    app or the website, you agree to these Terms.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Account and Sign-In</h2>
  <p>
    You may sign in with Apple or Google, or continue as a guest. You are
    responsible for activity under your account. Guest accounts store data
    locally on your device; signing in enables cloud sync across devices.
  </p>

  <h2>2. The App Is Free</h2>
  <p>
    Percolate is <strong>free</strong> to download and use. There is no
    subscription, no paywall, and no in-app purchase. Every feature &mdash;
    your shelf, the cupping log, label scanning, the flavor quiz, and the
    Year in Coffee recap &mdash; is included at no cost. Our only revenue comes
    from the affiliate links described below.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Affiliate Links and Roaster Disclosure</h2>
  <p>
    Coffee detail pages and selected articles may include
    <strong>&ldquo;Buy from&rdquo;</strong> links to roasters and specialty
    retailers. These are affiliate links: when you click one and complete a
    purchase, we may earn a small commission. <strong>This does not affect the
    price you pay.</strong>
  </p>
  <p>
    Affiliate links are clearly indicated on the page where they appear.
    Percolate is not a roaster or retailer and does not sell, roast, distribute,
    or ship coffee. Your purchase contract is with the roaster or retailer, and
    any questions about pricing, shipping, returns, or product freshness must be
    directed to them.
  </p>
  <p>
    This disclosure is provided in accordance with the FTC's
    <em>Guides Concerning the Use of Endorsements and Testimonials in Advertising</em>.
  </p>

  <h2>4. User Content</h2>
  <p>
    You retain ownership of content you create on Percolate, including
    cupping logs, ratings, private notes, community posts, and any reviews. By
    publishing a rating or any other content that you make public, you grant
    Percolate a non-exclusive, royalty-free, worldwide license to host, display,
    and distribute that content within the app and on the website for the
    purpose of operating the service.
  </p>
  <p>
    You may delete your public content at any time. Private notes and cupping
    logs remain solely under your control and are not licensed to us beyond
    what is necessary to operate the app.
  </p>
  <p>
    You agree not to submit content that is unlawful, defamatory, obscene,
    harassing, abusive, objectionable, or infringes on the intellectual
    property rights of others. We have zero tolerance for objectionable
    content or abusive behavior.
  </p>
  <p>
    Any user can report content through the in-app "Report" button. We review
    reports within 24 hours and will remove violating content and, where
    appropriate, restrict or terminate the offending account. We reserve the
    right to remove content at our discretion.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Recommendations</h2>
  <p>
    The pick, similarity matches, and flavor suggestions are
    best-effort, based on catalog data and our taste-profile model. Personal
    taste perception varies, and a coffee changes as the bag rests and you dial
    in your grind and brew. Treat suggestions as a starting point.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Acceptable Use</h2>
  <p>
    No abuse, scraping, reverse-engineering, or interference with the service.
    We may suspend or terminate accounts that violate these Terms.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Intellectual Property</h2>
  <p>
    The Percolate name, logo, design, and code are our property. Roaster
    names, coffee names, product names, and bag imagery are the
    property of their respective owners and are used for informational and
    identification purposes only.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
  <p>
    Percolate is provided "AS IS" and "AS AVAILABLE" without warranties
    of any kind, express or implied. Tasting notes, origin, process, and roast
    information are general reference and may not reflect every
    batch, harvest, or roast date. We make no claims about the suitability
    or compatibility of any coffee with any individual's preferences or health.
    If you have a known caffeine sensitivity or food allergy, consult the
    roaster or manufacturer before purchasing.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Limitation of Liability</h2>
  <p>
    To the maximum extent permitted by law, our total liability for any claim
    related to the app or the website shall not exceed the amount you paid to
    us in the prior twelve months. We are not liable for any indirect,
    incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages arising from or
    related to your use of the service, including loss of data.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Account Deletion</h2>
  <p>
    You may delete your account at any time from the Profile screen within
    the app. This permanently removes all your data and cannot be undone.
    Percolate is free, so there is no subscription to cancel.
  </p>

  <h2>11. Changes to These Terms</h2>
  <p>
    We may update these Terms from time to time. Material changes will be
    communicated through the app. Continued use after changes constitutes
    acceptance of the revised Terms.
  </p>

  <h2>12. Contact</h2>
  <p>
    For questions about these Terms, contact us at:
    <a href={`mailto:${SITE.supportEmail}`}>{SITE.supportEmail}</a>
  </p>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
